HEADWORD: Ceylanite
<hw>Cey"lan*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>Ceylan</ets> Ceylon.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A dingy blue, or
grayish black, variety of spinel. It is also called
<altname>pleonaste</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ceylonite</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

